For the greatest dry white wines of the world, one must look to Burgundy with its Montrachets, Chablis, Corton Charlemagnes and Pouilly Fuisses. They may lack the fruity bouquet of the German wines, but they compensate with fantastic breed, airy lightness and subtle finesse. Each of these wines are top flight with- in their class, having passed the test of our tasting panel gloriously. They will bring joy to the palate of discriminating drinkers of white wine—and not unim- portantly, represent the best values, dollar for dollar, of any collection of white Burgundies available any- where in the United States.
